hddb: the simple Haskell Document Database 

a simple sqlite-powered document tracker for the command-line

=== Installation ===

you will need to install the following BUILD dependencies:

    * GHC:          http://www.haskell.org/ghc/        
    * HDBC-Sqlite3: http://hackage.haskell.org/package/HDBC-sqlite3

you will need to install the following RUN-TIME dependencies:

    * Sqlite3:      http://www.sqlite.org

to build, simply run:

    $ make

to install, run:

    # make install

alternatively, control the install location with the 'PREFIX' and 'DESTDIR'
environment variables (or simply edit the Makefile).

Also, configure Config.hs as you wish *before* the build

=== Using ===

After building and installing,

    $ hddb help

also,

    $ man hddb

